  <thing id="cSpellswd" name="Spellsword" description="{b}Special{/b}: Must have defeated a foe through force of arms alone, without recourse to spellcasting.\n\nThe dream of melding magic and weaponplay is fulfilled in the person of the spellsword. A student of both arcane rituals and martial techniques, the spellsword gradually learns to cast spells in armor with less chance of failure. Moreover, he can cast spells through his weapon, bypassing his opponent&#146;s defenses.\n\nDespite the class&#146;s name, a spellsword can use any weapon or even switch weapons. &#147;Spellaxe,&#148; &#147;spellspear,&#148; and other appellations for this prestige class are certainly possible but not commonly used. The requirements for this prestige class make it most attractive to multiclass wizard/fighters or sorcerer/fighters, although bard/fighters can meet the requirements just as easily.\n\nFeared by other martial characters because of his ability to use spells, and feared by spellcasters because of his ability to cast those spells while wearing armor, a spellsword often walks the world alone.\n\n{b}Source{/b}: Complete Warrior" compset="ClassLevel" maxlimit="10">
    <usesource source="CompWarrio"/>
    <tag group="ClassType" tag="Prestige"/>
    <bootstrap thing="cHelpSpS"></bootstrap>
    <link linkage="helper" thing="cHelpSpS"/>
    <exprreq message="Knowledge (Arcana) 6 ranks required."><![CDATA[#skillranks[kKnowArcan] >= 6]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Proficiency with all Martial weapons required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fWepMart] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Simple Weapon Proficiency required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fSimple] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Armor Proficiency (Light) required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fArmLight] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Armor Proficiency (Medium) required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fArmMedium] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Armor Proficiency (Heavy) required."><![CDATA[#hasfeat[fArmHeavy] <> 0]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Ability to cast 2nd-level Arcane spells required."><![CDATA[tagcount[Hero.Arcane] >= 2 + 1]]></exprreq>
    <exprreq message="Base attack bonus +4 required."><![CDATA[child[Attack].field[tAtkBase].value >= 4]]></exprreq>
    </thing>
  <thing id="cSpSIgSpF1" name="Ignore Spell Failure 10%" description="Beginning at 1st level, a spell sword&#146;s hard work and practice at merging spellcraft with weaponplay starts to pay off. As an extraordinary ability, he ignores a portion of the arcane spell failure chance associated with using armor. This reduction starts at 10% and gradually increases to 30%, as shown on the class table. A spellsword subtracts the given percentage value from his total spell failure chance, if any. For instance, a character wearing scale mail and carrying a small shield normally has a spell failure chance of 30%, but this drops to only 20% for a 1st-level spellsword." compset="ClSpecial" summary="Arcane spell failure chance from armor/shields is reduced.">
    <comment>Eval. (Done)</comment>
    <tag group="AbilType" tag="Extra"/>
    <tag group="SpecSource" tag="cHelpSpS"/>
    <tag group="ClSpecWhen" tag="1"/>
    <eval phase="Final" priority="10001"><![CDATA[var reduce as number
var level as number
level = field[xTotalLev].value
if (level >= 9) then
  reduce = 30
elseif (level >= 7) then
  reduce = 25
elseif (level >= 5) then
  reduce = 20
elseif (level >= 3) then
  reduce = 15
else
  reduce = 10
endif

foreach pick in hero from BaseClHelp where "CasterSrc.Arcane"
  each.field[cArcFail].value -= reduce
  each.field[cArcFail].value = maximum(each.field[cArcFail].value, 0)
nexteach

field[livename].text = "Ignore Spell Failure " & reduce & "%"]]></eval>
    </thing>
