  <thing id="sHexDetScr" name="Detect Scrying" description="You immediately become aware of any attempt to observe you by means of a divination (scrying) spell or effect. The spell&#146;s area {b}(a 40-ft.-radius emanation){/b} radiates from you and moves as you move. You know the location of every magical sensor within the spell&#146;s area.\n\nIf the scrying attempt originates within the area, you also know its location; otherwise, you and the scrier immediately make opposed caster level checks (1d20 + caster level). If you at least match the scrier&#146;s result, you get a visual image of the scrier and an accurate sense of his or her direction and distance from you.\n\n{i}Material Component{/i}: A small piece of mirror and a miniature brass hearing trumpet." compset="Spell" summary="Alerts you of magical eavesdropping.">
